The Minister of Employment and Labour Thulas Nxesi  briefs the country on back-to-work readiness. This, as a result of the country moving from COVID-19 Level 5 which requires the most serious response and drastic measures to Level 4 which results in more businesses and industries opening and more South Africans having to go back to work. The briefing takes place in Hatfield, Pretoria. In the video below, Minister of Employment Thulas Nxesi briefs media on Sunday:   The graphic below outlines the Level 4 lockdown restrictions 